==English==

===Etymology===
Old English [[growan|grōwan]], from Germanic ''*grō-''. Cognate with Dutch [[groeien]]. Compare [[grass]], [[green]].

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/ɡrəʊ/}}, {{SAMPA|/gr@U/}}
*{{audio|en-us-grow.ogg|Audio (US)}}
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-əʊ|-əʊ]]

===Verb===
{{en-verb|grows|growing|grew|grown}}

# {{intransitive}} To [[become]] [[bigger]].
#: ''Children '''grow''' quickly.''
# {{intransitive}} To [[appear]] or [[sprout]].
#: ''The plant began to '''grow'''.''
#: ''A long tail began to '''grow''' from his backside.''
# {{transitive}} To cause something to become bigger, especially plants.
#: ''He '''grows''' peppers and squash each summer in his garden.''

